According to UK tabloid 'The Sun,' the future British King is considering taking a role in the upcoming James Bond film "Bond 25". An insider says the role was offered to him when he recently visited the film's production set. Prince Charles is the epitome of everything British, perfect for a cameo role and Bond fans worldwide would absolutely love it, Production source, via 'The Sun'. The source adds that an appearance by Prince Charles could help generate significant buzz for the movie, which has suffered multiple setbacks. The producers are desperate to sign him. It is no secret that the film has suffered a number of setbacks but landing a Royal could be just what the movie needs, Production source, via 'The Sun'.'Bond 25,' which marks Daniel Craig's final movie as James Bond. Bond 25 is set to hit the big screen in April 2020. 